23/01/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- The government announced Thursday (22 January) that police have arrested 19 members of an organisation that may have smuggled 270 people into Western European countries. The illegal immigrants allegedly were taken through Bosnia and Herzegovina, Croatia, and Slovenia to their final destinations, in Austria, Germany, Italy and Switzerland. During a raid, police seized several Albanian, Bulgarian, Macedonian, and Turkish passports, more than 1,000 rounds of ammunition, a rifle, and two hand grenades. (AFP - 22/01/04)
